git-svn-id: https://subversion.assembla.com/svn/qmcdev/trunk@6397 e5b18d87-469d-4833-9cc0-8cdfa06e9491

Modified simplex parameter selection

Defined a simplex variable:
    (2nd der.) / (1st der.)**2.

Parameters are sorted according to this variable. The lowest parameters are
selected for simplex optimization.

Parameters with values larger than 1 shouldn't be used in simplex. These
parameters are bracketed by the differentiation and should be left to the
gradient optimization. Accordingly, I wrote some code for that in this commit,
but it's currently commented.

Eliminating all parameters with simplex variables higher than 1 could lead to
exceedingly small parameter sets, perhaps 1 or 2 parameters.

Correct selection probabilities for clusters in the CCMC full non-composite algorithm.

The selection probability includes the number of clusters that are generated by
a processor in a single timestep.  This was correctly set for the original
algorithm but not for the full non-composite algorithm where the number of
attempts is divided between stochastic selection of composite clusters and
deterministic selection of single excitors.

svn-origin-rev: 14646
travis: exclude gcc 6 debug build, internal compiler error when compiling zrhf.cpp

1. Adds (indirect) block buffers for accessing data blocks
   (dbcsr_block_buffers.F).
   * By default there is no change. Buffers are not used unless
     explicitly enabled.
   * By using buffers it is now possible to avoid dubious pointer hacks
     with compilers that do not support pointer rank remapping
   * CP2K pointers can be indirect (i.e., not point directly into matrix
     storage: allows for other storage types)
2. Moves dbcsr_data_obj and dbcsr_scalar_type methods into separate
   dbcsr_data_methods.F files. Also adds some helper subroutines
   (reallocation, ...).
3. Updates block buffer support in iterator and block access routines.
   Iterator now also supports a read-only specification (no buffer
   flushing).
4. Flushing buffers added where needed
5. Unifies pointer rank remapping and places it in dbcsr_ptr_util.F.
6. Updates a few block operations (1D-2D data copy/transposes).
7. Cleans up make dense/undense data
